            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This has been reported many times for various features. We don't need more reports, we need a Windows user to actually work on fixing this.\n\nRelated:\n\n- #25791\n- #28384 \n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25033#issuecomment-1715407131\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/23639#issuecomment-1548647316\n\n\n# Proposal\n\nThe general solution that I have proposed is, Nvim should always use `/` slashes everywhere, and only for a few specific cases it should \"convert\" to `\\` slashes just-in-time, for very specific cases.\n\n1. Internally and everywhere, change to `/` slashes. Update all the tests.\n2. In targeted followup PRs, change specific functions and features that really want `\\` slashes. Make them call a \"covert slashes\" function just-in-time.",
